{"word":"ἐκφορέω","slug":"ἐκφορέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐκφορέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>= <a href='S:ἐκφέρω'><el>ἐκφέρω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to carry out</i> a corpse for burial, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>:—generally <i>to carry out</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to take out with one</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to move forth</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to carry quite out, leave none behind</i>, of earth dug from a trench, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be cast on shore</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}